## SPRINT PLAN

Break the implementation into 3–4 sprints. Each sprint must deliver sizable, complete, end-to-end testable features — do not defer integration or testing to the end. Working software at the end of every sprint, not just components.

For each sprint, define:
- What is delivered (specific, demoable functionality)
- **Acceptance/test criteria** — specify concretely how completion is verified (e.g., a documented manual demo script with expected outputs, automated unit/integration tests for backend and ML logic, or both). State which form of verification applies to which deliverable; do not leave "tested" undefined.

---

## DEPLOYMENT

- Single container deployment to Google Cloud Run.
- Optimize for lowest cost (e.g., scale-to-zero, minimal instance sizing, efficient image build).
- Clean internal repo structure: frontend module, backend module, ML modules — single repo, multiple modules, one deployable.

